---
description: Common area keyword parameters usable across most RMF areas
---

These modifiers are accepted by most areas (some may be ignored depending on area type):

- `key <key> <command>` — run command when area highlighted and key pressed.
- `ckey <key> <cvar> <falsecmd> <truecmd>` — conditional key bind while highlighted.
- `ikey <action> <command>` — action-based bind while highlighted.
- `tint <colour>` — base tint filter.
- `atint <colour>` — highlight tint when hovered.
- `btint <colour>` — background fill tint (area-dependent).
- `ctint <colour>` / `dtint <colour>` — additional highlight/diff tints (area-dependent).
- `noshade` — disable automatic shading.
- `noscale` — disable auto scaling of bolt offsets.
- `border <width> <lineWidth> <lineColour>` — area border.
- `width <value>` / `height <value>` — override size.
- `cvar <cvar>` — associate a console variable.
- `cvari <cvar>` — integer console variable association.
- `inc <value>` — keyboard step size for value changes.
- `mod <value>` — modulus (wrap-around) for values.
- `tip <text>` — tooltip text.
- `xoff <value>` / `yoff <value>` — pixel offsets (often for bolted areas).
- `tab` — use next tab stop (from `<tab>` layout).
- `noborder` — disable border even if defaults define one.
- `bolt <bolt>` — bolt to most recent ghoul model bolt.
- `bbolt <bolt>` — bolt to background ghoul model bolt.
- `align <left|center|right>` — override page alignment.

